Program_Policies: To earn an undergraduate certificate in Space Systems Engineering, a minimum of 12 credits is required.; Students must earn a C grade or better in each of the courses to continue with the certificate.; Students must complete an application. A project report must be submitted adhering to SPSYS Certificate formatting and systems content guidelines.; Prerequisites Required.
